adjectives.description: deliverable (comparative more deliverable, superlative most deliverable)

examples: The packages were not deliverable because the roads had flooded out.

entries.meaning: (business, management) The tangible end product; that which will be delivered.
examples: Due to inclement weather, we will be unable to provide our deliverables.
We packaged the deliverable, a program called FLOOD.EXE, in an installer file.
